The course consists various topics related toevent management,  accessibility, safety regulations, planning and operationg safe environments, legislation and permits.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main aim of the course is to give to the participants the overview and knowledge about events safety and accessibility and explain how these theories and principles work in practice, including the viewpoints of the participants, audience and organisers.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: - has a basic knowledge of event accessibility - understands the main tasks and terminology of events safety and security - understands the principles of safety planning and risk management -  is familiar with the Estonian legislation concerning the safety of event management and venues - can prepare an application for a public event permit.
